text: Liesbeth Migchelsen (11 March 1971 - 27 May 2020) was a Dutch footballer. She represented the Netherlands women's national team 95 times between 1990 and 2008. Micgchelsen played in Germany for FFC Heike Rheine and in The Netherlands for S.V. Fortuna Wormerveer and AZ Alkmaar. She coached Australian W-League team Canberra United FC from 2013 to 2014. Migchelsen was born in Harderwijk, Netherlands. She died on 27 May 2020 of cancer, aged 49.Oud- voetbalster Liesbeth Migchelsen overleden ==International goals== :Scores and results list the Netherlands goal tally first.
